{
  "name": "Wyvern Poison (Injury)",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>This &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} must be harvested from a dead or &amp;Reference[incapacitated]{incapacitated} wyvern. A creature subjected to this &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} must make a [[/save con 15 format=long]], taking 24 (7d6) &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>Injury.</strong> Injury &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} can be applied to weapons, ammunition, trap components, and other objects that deal &amp;Reference[piercing]{piercing} or &amp;Reference[slashing]{slashing} damage and remains potent until delivered through a wound or washed off. A creature that takes &amp;Reference[piercing]{piercing} or &amp;Reference[slashing]{slashing} damage from an object coated with the &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} is exposed to its effects.</p>\n</div>",
